dct_description_sm: Published at the War Office, 1929 ; Compiled and drawn at W.O., heliographed at O.S. and printed at W.O. 1929.
Relief shown by contours, gradient tints, spot heights; depths by soundings.
3 ancillary maps in bottom margin: 1) Index to boundaries, 2) Index to adjoining sheets, and 3) Relative reliability [with legend].

Shows various roads and paths, railroads (including projected and under construction), various names (regional, topographical, tribal names, etc.), cities and towns, canals, waterways (including unsurveyed), plains liable to flooding, marshland, ruins, water sources, telegraph stations, trigonometrical stations, limits of navigation, boundaries.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain, War Office., General Staff., Geographical Section.
